sql:
SELECT COUNT(stock_id) AS total_listed_stocks
FROM stock_exchange_stocks
WHERE exchange_id = 0;

SELECT name 
FROM stocks 
ORDER BY name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "Top-performing stocks" refers to stocks with the highest percentage increase in price; 
- "Over the last 30 days" means from the current date to 30 days ago;
- "Average market capitalization" and "average volume" refer to the mean values of market capitalization and volume for the selected stocks;
- "Number of portfolios they are part of" refers to the count of unique portfolios that hold these stocks.
